text: The Trademark Reporter is a bimonthly peer-reviewed academic journal covering trademark law and related topics. It was first established in 1911 and is published by the International Trademark Association. Articles published by the journal have been cited by different courts.United States Supreme Court: Two Pesos v. Taco Cabana, 505 U.S. 763 (1992)TTAB Decision: ProMark Brands Inc. and H.J. Heinz Company v.
